Please answer the below core-java Questions:

What is programing language?
A.
A programming language is a vocabulary and set of grammatical rules used to instruct a computer or computing device to perform specific
tasks.
The term programming language usually refers to high-level languages such as BASIC, C, C++, COBOL, Java, FORTRAN, Ada, and Pascal.
-Java is one of the most popular programming language, created in 1995, it is owned by Oracle, and more than 3 billion devices run java.


What jdk contains or composed of and define each components?
A.
1-JRE (Java Run Time): it is a software platform where all the Java Source codes are executed. it is also responsible for integrating the software
 plugins, jar files, and support libraries necessary for the source code to run, it contains the JVM and JIT,
 -JVM (Java Virtual Machine) which is a software tool responsible for creating a run-time environment for the Java source code to run.
 -JIT (Just In Time): it improves the performance of Java applications by compiling bytecodes to native machine code at run time
2-Compiler
3-Debugger
4-Disassembler



What is IDE?
A. IDE stands for integrated Development Environment, it is is a software application that helps programmers develop software code
efficiently. It increases developer productivity by combining capabilities such as software editing, building, testing, and packaging
 in an easy-to-use application.



What are the IDEs available in the market to support java?
A.
Eclipse, Intellij IDEA, MyEclipse IDE, BlueJ IDE, Xcode IDE, JDeveloper IDE, JCreator IDE....


Explain the entire java life cycle.
There are two main stages in the life cycle of a java program:
Compile time: During the compile time we create our java code and  type the program in a text-editor, we have to save the file (the file
must be saved with .java extension), and we call it a source code. It will go throw the compiler and the same file will go throw the JIT be
transformed into a.class file which is full of binaries.
Run time: during this step the binaries generated by the compiler will go throw the JIT compiler and will be transformed into a native code
that the machine understands and the code runs.

