Does java support multiple inheritance, explain why or why not?
no, because in java a class can not inherit from 2 classes or more, it can only inherits from a single class


What is method overloading and when it happens?
Method overloading occurs when two or more methods in one class have the same method name but different
parameters. it happens during the compiling time

Explain exceptions in java and how to handle it?
exceptions are the errors that we have in java, we have two types of exceptions: checked and unchecked or we call
them also Run time exceptions and compile time exceptions.
-To handle exceptions in java we can either use try and catch block, or use throws keyword in the method signature.

What is static keyword in java? How it has been used in variables and methods ?
The static keyword is an inaccessible modifier for methods and attributes, it makes any attribute belonging  to
a class, for every instance of this class created, these static members remain the same, they can not be changed
or modified.
in order to call any static attributes we don't need to create an object, we just need to use a name of a
class. and than call the attributes.

What is final and how it has been used variables and methods?
Final is a non access modifier used for classes, attributes and methods, which makes them non-changeable.
the impact of it for variables is we cannot reassign it
The impact of final for method is it cannot be overrided
the impact of final to à class is class cannot be inherited


What is final, finally and finalize?
-Final is a non access modifier used for classes, attributes and methods, which makes them non-changeable.
the impact of it for variables is we cannot reassign it
The impact of final for method is it cannot be overrided
the impact of final to à class is class cannot be inherited
-Finally is a keyword that is used after try and catch block, it is a block that is executed anyway.
-Finalize is a method that is used in garbage collection

